Eman's Blog https://emandeguzman.github.io/posts/waitfor/ -<h2 id="motivation">Motivation</h2>
<p>With the use of defer/async to load javascipts, it has become apparent that we must make sure that the javascript function, object, variables are loaded before referring to the those items.<br>
waitFor checks for the presence of these items then runs the provided callback function (if any) once the checked item is loaded and ready for use.<br>
waitFor returns a Promise so it can also be used in a promise chain. This is especially usefull when checking for existence of a function since you cannot reference a non-defined function in the callback.</p>
<h2 id="syntax">Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>waitFor(&lt;item to check&gt;, &lt;item type&gt;, [callback function])
</code></pre>
<h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Parameter</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
<th>Default</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>item to check</td>
<td>string</td>
<td>The name of the item to check</td>
<td>&lt;required&gt;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>item type</td>
<td>string</td>
<td>The type of the item being checked. This is the value of the <strong>typeof</strong> operation on the <strong>item</strong></td>
<td>&lt;required&gt;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>callback</td>
<td>function</td>
<td>The callback function to be called after the <strong>item</strong> is determined to be defined</td>
<td>[optional]</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2 id="return-value">Return Value</h2>
<ul>
<li>waitFor returns a resolved promise object once the typeof operation on the <strong>item</strong> is equal to that of the passed <strong>item type</strong>.</li>
<li>If the specified <strong>item type</strong> is not correct, waitFor will return a rejected promise.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="warning">Warning</h2>
<p>waitFor will not run the callback function nore return a promise <strong>item to check</strong> is undefined.</p>
